{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place orange peel in mixing bowl and grate <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add sugar and grind <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl.","Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add butter, flour, rum, 10 g orange juice, reserved orange sugar and salt then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Tip out dough onto a lightly floured work surface and divide into quarters. Shape each quarter into a 16 cm long log (approx. Ø 3 cm). Wrap logs in cling film and place in freezer for 30 minutes to make dough firmer and easier to cut.","Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper and prepare 2 more sheets of baking paper.","Cut dough into 7 mm wide slices and place on prepared baking tray and extra baking paper sheets. Bake biscuits on baking tray for 12 minutes (180°C). Remove cooked biscuits on baking paper and replace with second sheet of baking paper with biscuits. Bake second batch for 12 minutes (180°C) then allow to cool. Repeat with final batch of biscuits.","Mix icing sugar and 20 g orange juice in a small bowl. Once biscuits are cool, decorate with icing. Allow icing to set before serving or store in an airtight container."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 orange, unwaxed, thin peelings of skin and 30 g juice","120 g sugar","150 g blanched almonds","130 g unsalted butter, cold, diced","200 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","20 g rum","110 g icing sugar"]}],"id":"r254894","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-wEGLM8o-ySM\/XZWpx3jf4VI\/AAAAAAAAfO8\/15taXO801HwFfWgIxpPVeHf_tZ_0YODqQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6NruZyoeG8eGlgZ6.png","title":"Orange Burst Biscuits","publishedAt":"2017-12-11T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"2 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"5 g","calories":"189 kJ \/ 45 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, baking tray, baking paper, airtight container, freezer, oven","basicInfo":["me